abstract: Official results of Iran's Parliamentary elections are kept under wraps by Interior Ministry, leaving precise character of new government unclear; success of candidates supporting incumbent moderate government appears overwhelming in Tehran, but prohibition of political parties makes gauging affiliations of winners outside capital challenging.
lead_paragraph: Five days after national elections, the Interior Ministry has yet to release official detailed results, and the picture outside Tehran remains unclear.

headline.main: Doubts Rise in Iran About Conclusive Election Results
headline.print_headline: Full Picture of Iran Vote Is Still Murky 5 Days Later
